== Effectiveness of INA ==

Every historian I'm acquainted with who has an opinion on the subject disparages the effectiveness of the INA, pointing out that the men recruited into it faced the alternative of brutal treatment in a POW camp and most deserted back to the British at the first opportunity. For example, Max Hastings has discussed this in his book, ''Retribution.''  [[Special:Contributions/97.123.121.16|97.123.121.16]] ([[User talk:97.123.121.16|talk]]) 01:31, 22 January 2010 (UTC)

:Allow me to direct you to Hugh Toye's book published in 1959 and Peter Fay's book in 1993 for a start.[[User:rueben_lys|rueben_lys]] ([[User talk:rueben_lys|talk]] '''·''' [[Special:Contribs/rueben_lys|contribs]]) 11:40, 1 October 2015 (UTC)

